# importdoc

> **Advanced Import Diagnostic Tool for Python**  
Deep, automated import analysis for Python projects ‚Äî with subprocess-safe imports, circular dependency detection, auto-fix suggestions, AST-based symbol resolution, and CI-ready JSON output.

---

## üöÄ Features

| Capability | Description |
|----------|-------------|
üîç **Import graph discovery** | Recursively maps and validates imports across a project  
üß† **AST-based analysis** | Detects missing imports, wrong module paths, and unresolved symbols  
‚ö° **Subprocess safe imports** | Imports each module in a sandboxed subprocess (timeout safe)  
üõë **Circular import detection** | Identifies dependency cycles with stack traces  
üõ†Ô∏è **Automated fix suggestions** | Suggest proper import paths + generate JSON patches  
üìä **JSON diagnostic mode** | CI-friendly structured reports  
üì¶ **Cache & telemetry** | Optional cache + performance metrics  
üõ°Ô∏è **Safe mode** | Avoids dangerous imports outside venv by default  
üìà **Graph export** | DOT dependency graph generation (Graphviz)  

---

## üì¶ Installation

### PyPI

```bash
pip install importdoc

Development (editable)

pip uninstall importdoc -y
pip install -e .


---

üîß CLI Usage

Basic usage

importdoc your_package

Running in a project dir

importdoc your_package --dir .

Allow root (CI / Docker)

importdoc your_package --allow-root

Enable full diagnostics

importdoc your_package --verbose --enable-cache --enable-telemetry

JSON output (CI pipelines)

importdoc your_package --json > import_report.json

Auto-fix suggestions

importdoc your_package --generate-fixes --fix-output fixes.json

Dependency graph (Graphviz)

importdoc your_package --graph --dot-file imports.dot
dot -Tpng imports.dot -o graph.png


---

üß™ Example Output (Success)

üéâ ALL MODULES IMPORTED SUCCESSFULLY!
‚ú® Production-ready: No import issues detected

üö® Example Output (Import Error)

üö® FAILED TO IMPORT: myapp.models.user
üî• ROOT CAUSE: ImportError: cannot import name 'Profile' from 'myapp.profile'
üìä Evidence:
  - myapp/profile.py:15: class Profile
üí° Suggested Fixes:
  1. from myapp.profile import Profile
üß† Confidence: 9/10


---

‚öôÔ∏è Options Summary

Flag	Purpose

--continue-on-error	Never stop on failures
--parallel N	Parallel subprocess imports
--json	JSON report mode
--graph	Create DOT graph
--no-safe-mode	Allow global environment imports
--enable-cache	Speed up repeated runs
--dev-trace	Debug import chain tracing


Run full help:

importdoc --help


---

üõ°Ô∏è CI/CD Usage

GitHub Actions

- name: Run import diagnostics
  run: importdoc mypkg --json --continue-on-error > import_report.json


---

üß† When to Use importdoc

Situation	importdoc saves you

‚ùì Random import failures	‚úÖ Pinpoints real source
üîÅ Circular imports	‚úÖ Finds cycles with stack trace
‚öôÔ∏è Large refactors	‚úÖ Detects broken import paths
ü§ñ CI safety	‚úÖ Reports without executing package runtime logic
üì¶ Package release testing	‚úÖ Ensures import reliability



---

üß© Project Structure Example

yourproject/
 ‚îú‚îÄ src/
 ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ yourpackage/
 ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ __init__.py
 ‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ ...
 ‚îî‚îÄ tests/

Run:

importdoc yourpackage --dir ./src


